.( Tron 0xF: game )

2 8 THRU

( Rudder increments)

 \ Coordinate increments.
 \ Double constants are used to update the coordinate
 \ increments faster.

  1  0 2CONSTANT UP-INCS
 -1  0 2CONSTANT DOWN-INCS
  0 -1 2CONSTANT LEFT-INCS
  0  1 2CONSTANT RIGHT-INCS

( Rudder 1)

: HUMAN-RUDDER1  ( -- n1 n2 )

  \ Update the coordinate increments of player 1.
  \ Human control.

  UP-K1 @ PRESSED?
  IF   XINC1 @ IF  UP-INCS XINC1 2!     THEN  EXIT  THEN
  DOWN-K1 @ PRESSED?
  IF   XINC1 @ IF  DOWN-INCS XINC1 2!   THEN  EXIT  THEN
  LEFT-K1 @ PRESSED?
  IF   YINC1 @ IF  LEFT-INCS XINC1 2!   THEN  EXIT  THEN
  RIGHT-K1 @ PRESSED?
  IF   YINC1 @ IF  RIGHT-INCS XINC1 2!  THEN  EXIT  THEN  ;

DEFER RUDDER1  ( -- )  ' HUMAN-RUDDER1 IS RUDDER1

: MOVE1  ( -- )

  \ Update the coordinates of player 1.

  RUDDER1  XINC1 @ XC1 +!  YINC1 @ YC1 +!  ;

( Rudder 2)

: HUMAN-RUDDER2  ( -- )

  \ Update the coordinate increments of player 2.
  \ Human control.

  UP-K2 @ PRESSED?
  IF   XINC2 @ IF  UP-INCS XINC2 2!     THEN  EXIT  THEN
  DOWN-K2 @ PRESSED?
  IF   XINC2 @ IF  DOWN-INCS XINC2 2!   THEN  EXIT  THEN
  LEFT-K2 @ PRESSED?
  IF   YINC2 @ IF  LEFT-INCS XINC2 2!   THEN  EXIT  THEN
  RIGHT-K2 @ PRESSED?
  IF   YINC2 @ IF  RIGHT-INCS XINC2 2!  THEN  EXIT  THEN  ;
  
DEFER RUDDER2  ( -- )  ' HUMAN-RUDDER2 IS RUDDER2

: MOVE2  ( -- ) 
  
  \ Update the coordinates of player 2.

  RUDDER2  XINC2 @ XC2 +!  YINC2 @ YC2 +!  ;

( Rudder 3)

: HUMAN-RUDDER3  ( -- n1 n2 )

  \ Update the coordinate increments of player 3.
